\subsection{Purpose of the project}
\label{sec:orgheadline2}
Explore ways of using plain text for personal organising, managing
information, and communicating - then writing a simple guide or set of
how-to notes.

\subsection{Overview of plain text}
\label{sec:orgheadline3}
Write a section drawing on:

\begin{itemize}
\item \href{http://plaintext-productivity.net/}{Introduction | Plaintext Productivity} 
   todo.txt, notes and organising. How to use with Windows.
\item \href{http://blog.scottlowe.org/2015/04/06/plain-text-productivity-experiment/}{The Plain Text Productivity Experiment · Scott's Weblog}
\item \href{https://zapier.com/blog/plain-text-files-for-productivity/}{10 Plain Text Files You Should Have on Your Desktop for Higher Productivity}
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Using plain text in practice}
\label{sec:orgheadline4}
Examples of using plain text

\begin{itemize}
\item Todo lists
\item Project planning
\item Collaborative documents
\item Calendars
\end{itemize}

Key elements of plain text

\begin{itemize}
\item Syntax
\item File extensions
\item Desktop and mobile apps to provide an interface with text files
\end{itemize}

