\section{Dropbox}
\label{sec:orgheadline39}
\begin{itemize}
\item \href{https://www.dropbox.com/}{Dropbox}
\end{itemize}

\begin{quote}
Dropbox works the way you do Get to all your files from anywhere, on
any device, and share them with anyone.
\end{quote}

\subsection{Dropbox on mobile devices}
\label{sec:orgheadline38}
\begin{itemize}
\item Linking applications to your Dropbox folder
\end{itemize}

After installing Dropbox on your mobile device you can authorize other
mobile applications on your device to allow access to your Dropbox
folder, by linking the the application to your Dropbox folder and
authorizing the application.

This creates an App folder in your Dropbox and inside it another folder
with the name of the Application you authorized

\begin{itemize}
\item Manually adding Dropbox account details to an application
\end{itemize}

Some applications require you to manually enter your Dropbox username
and password.
